
If arp-scan is not installed, execute: sudo apt-get install arp-scan

First to install the software arp-scan, and then run the command:

$ arp-scan --interface=wlan0 --localnet

In this example, our network interface is Wlan0, but it can change.

How to make this in C++ or C?

It is easy, should use the command:

system("command > fileStore").

Where fileStore go to store the IPs on the Network. Enjoy!